Comparison between 16S and COI data (Jitterplot)

# Bacteria:

# Reads:
bac_reads_box <- bacteria %>% 
  select(ID, Taxon, Status, BacteriaReads, Year) %>% 
  filter(Year != "NA")

bac_reads_box$Year <- as.numeric(bac_reads_box$Year)

b1_count <- bac_reads_box %>% 
  mutate(category = cut(Year, breaks = c(-Inf, 1900, 1950, 2000, 2020, Inf), labels = c("<1900","1900-1950","1951-2000","2001-2020","Contemporary"))) %>%
  count(category) %>% 
  ungroup() %>% 
  unite("label",category, n, sep = "<br>n=", remove = F)

bac_reads <- bac_reads_box %>% 
  mutate(category = cut(Year, breaks = c(-Inf, 1900, 1950, 2000, 2020, Inf), labels = c("<1900","1900-1950","1951-2000","2001-2020","Contemporary"))) %>%  
  mutate(Group = cut(Year, breaks = c(-Inf, 1900, 1950, 2000, 2020, Inf), labels = c("veryold","old","medium","young","contemporary")))%>% 
  left_join(b1_count, by = "category")

### Test ###-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
bac_reads %>% 
  group_by(Group) %>% 
  summarise(mean = mean(BacteriaReads),
            sd = sd(BacteriaReads))
## # A tibble: 5  3
##   Group         mean    sd
##   <fct>        <dbl> <dbl>
## 1 veryold       232.  159.
## 2 old           261.  290.
## 3 medium        800. 1119.
## 4 young         726.  482.
## 5 contemporary 4979. 1722.
krus_bac_reads <- kruskal.test(BacteriaReads~Group, data = bac_reads)

dunn_bac_reads <- dunnTest(BacteriaReads~Group, data = bac_reads, method = "bonferroni")

dunn_bac_reads <- dunn_bac_reads$res

bac_reads_letters <- cldList(comparison = dunn_bac_reads$Comparison,
        p.value    = dunn_bac_reads$P.adj,
        threshold  = 0.05) %>% as.data.frame()

bac_reads_cld <- bac_reads %>% 
  group_by(Group) %>% 
  summarise(m = mean(BacteriaReads),
            max = max(BacteriaReads)) %>% 
  arrange(desc(m)) %>%

Box plots of relative prey abudance according to the dominating symbiont

set.seed(555)

prey_cont_matrix <- prey %>% 
  filter(Status == "Contemporary") %>% 
  select(starts_with("OTU"))

prey_cont_rarefy <- Rarefy(prey_cont_matrix, 1693)$otu.tab.rff %>% 
  as.data.frame()

prey_cont_rarefied <- prey %>% 
  select(-starts_with("OTU")) %>% 
  filter(Status == "Contemporary") %>%
  filter(PreyReads >= 1693) %>% 
  merge(prey_cont_rarefy, by = "row.names") %>% 
  as.data.frame()


insect_order_symbiont <- prey_cont_rarefied %>%
  select(-Row.names,-Number,-Taxon,-Status,-MuseumID,-Maturity,-Sex,-Continent,-Country,-Location,-ConditionOpisthosoma,-Year,-DominantSymbiont,-UnknownSymbiont,-TotalOTU,-PreyReads,-Category,-Green,-Yellow,-Orange,-Red,-Blue)  %>%
  pivot_longer(-ID, names_to = "OTU") %>% 
  left_join(prey_taxa, by = "OTU") %>% 
  left_join(prey, by ="ID") %>% 
  select(ID, OTU, value, Order, UnknownSymbiont) %>%
  group_by(ID, Order) %>%
  summarise(value = sum(value)) %>% 
  ungroup() %>% 
  group_by(ID) %>% 
  mutate(total = sum(value)) %>% 
  ungroup() %>% 
  mutate(rel_abund = 100*value/total) %>% 
  left_join(prey, by = "ID") %>% 
  select(ID, Order, rel_abund, DominantSymbiont) %>%
  mutate(pool = (Order == "Blattodea" |
         Order == "Diptera" |
         Order == "Hemiptera" |
         Order == "Hymenoptera" |
         Order == "Lepidoptera" |
         Order == "Orthoptera")) %>%
  mutate(Order = if_else(pool, Order, "Other (<3%)")) %>% # Other: less than 3% in total
  group_by(ID, Order) %>% 
  summarise(rel_abund = sum(rel_abund)) %>% 
  ungroup() %>% 
  left_join(prey_cont_rarefied, by = "ID") %>% 
  select(ID, Order, rel_abund, DominantSymbiont)
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'ID'. You can override using the `.groups`
## argument.
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'ID'. You can override using the `.groups`
## argument.
insect_order_symbiont %>%  # Count samples
  group_by(DominantSymbiont, ID) %>% 
  summarise(x = sum(rel_abund)) %>% 
  count(DominantSymbiont)
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'DominantSymbiont'. You can override using
## the `.groups` argument.

order <- insect_order_symbiont %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = Order, y = rel_abund))+
  geom_boxplot(aes(fill = DominantSymbiont))+
  labs(title = "<br><br>Relative abundance of the main insect orders in the gut content of *A. bruennichi*<br> according to the predominating symbiont<br><br>",
       x="",
       y="Relative abundance (%)",
       fill = "Predominant bacteria:")+

                    labels= c("*Mesoplasma sp.* (n=11)", "DUSA (n=18)"))+

        legend.key.size = unit(18, "pt"),

                                         color = "black"))+

  theme(axis.text.x = element_markdown(size = 18))+
